# Client Rules

## Components

- Preact (functional). Use `class` not `className`.
- Import CSS alongside component: `import './Component.css'`.
- UI primitives: `@src/client/components/ui/` (Button, Modal, Input, Badge, etc.).
- State/query patterns: prefer existing `@preact/signals` stores and shared API client cache before adding new libs.
- UI design standards: follow `@.cursor/rules/design-system.mdc` for tokens, states, accessibility, and i18n UI copy.
- Icon migration reference: `@docs/ICONS_PLAN.md`.

## Hooks

- `useTokenLimitCheck`, `useChapterTranslation`, `useUserRole`, `useTokenEstimate` — see `src/client/hooks/`.
- Contexts: `TokenUsageContext`, `ServiceHealthContext`.

## i18n

- `react-i18next`. Keys in `src/client/locales/` (en.json, ru.json, pl.json).
- Use `useTranslation()` hook. Add new keys to all locale files.

## Routing

- `preact-router`. Routes in `@src/client/AppRouter.tsx`.
- If client routes/navigation change, sync `@docs/ROUTES.md` in the same change.

## UI Change Checklist (Required for `src/client/**`)

- MUST reuse existing UI primitives before adding new visual patterns.
- MUST use tokens from `@src/client/styles/base/variables.css` instead of ad-hoc colors/sizing.
- MUST ensure interactive states exist: hover, focus-visible, disabled, loading (when applicable).
- MUST keep user-facing UI strings in i18n keys (`en/ru/pl`), not hardcoded literals.
- MUST verify changed UI for mobile/tablet/desktop viewports.
- MUST preserve minimum 44px touch target for mobile/tablet interactive controls.
- SHOULD avoid inline styles for reusable visual patterns.
